article.headline: Colgate 67, American 57
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Alvin Reed scored 17 points, including five 3-pointers, to lead Colgate to a 67-57 win over American Sunday. It was the Raiders (11-13) third straight win, while the Eagles (13-10) dropped its third straight. After American scored the opening basket, Colgate ran off nine straight points and never looked back. The Raiders led by as many as 12 points twice in the first half before taking a 34-22 halftime lead. In the second half, Colgate continued to dominate play leading by 25 points, 55-30, with 12:07 left. American scored the final 12 points of the contest after both benches were emptied. Andrew Zidar finished with 14 points and Kyle Roemer added 10 for Colgate. American was led by Andre Ingram with 16 points, and Raimondas Petrauskas with 14.
